      • quickSort

        public static void quickSort​(java.lang.Object[] array,
                             java.lang.Integer begin,
                             java.lang.Integer end)
        Quick Sort algorithm. To call the method in code just use: Sorting.quickSort(array of elements, begin index, end index); Example: Integer array with values like this: Integer[] tab = new Integer[6]; tab[0] = 10; tab[1] = 9; tab[2] = 8; tab[3] = 7; tab[4] = 6; tab[5] = 12; To sort tab array call the quickSort method from Sorting class: Sorting.quickSort(tab,0,5); Where 0 is index from which sorting starts and the 5 is index on which sorting ends.
        Parameters:
        array - Array which is going to be sorted. This array can only store Integer, Double etc. objects, primitive types not allowed.
        begin - Index of element from which sorting range starts. Must be Integer type.
        end - Index of element from which sorting range ends. Must be Integer type.
